text: The concave-crowned tree frog or Yunnan whipping frog (Polypedates impresus) is a frog. It lives in China, Laos, Thailand, and Vietnam. People have seen it between 600 and 1000 meters above sea level. This frog lives in grass on hills. Scientists believe this frog is not in danger of dying out because it lives in such a large place. ==First paper== * ==References== Category:Frogs of Asia
title: Polypedates impresus
